properties.Name: SwitchState
properties.Description:
The state of the switch.

Ex:
-  Open
-  Closed

Each set of contacts can be in one of two states: either 'closed' meaning the contacts are touching and electricity can flow between them, or 'open', meaning the contacts are separated and nonconducting.

Columns.Name: SwitchStateId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a switch state.

Columns.Name: SwitchStateName
Columns.Description: The name of a switch state.

Columns.Name: SwitchStateDescription
Columns.Description: The description of a switch state.
